BASH script and config collection
Author: Andreas Maunz, <andreas@maunz.de>
Date: 12/2012

Usage:
cd # change directory to $HOME
sudo apt-get install vim
git clone git://github.com/amaunz/home-bin
cd home-bin
./_init.sh # Copy files to $HOME

The last step uses vimdiff to merge changes manually, if files already exist on your system.
Learn about vimdiff here: http://goo.gl/7SH1I
